{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886044057,"sessionID":"ses_284f32f7bffefLseUVxkQaAaFx","part":{"id":"prt_d7b0e8b73001AhIcq4FjUNQVZE","messageID":"msg_d7b0dad4d001FVTG5dILQ6ldwu","sessionID":"ses_284f32f7bffefLseUVxkQaAaFx","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-1356c1a09a4f4403b4612026e12d1411","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-032 |\n| Module | docker |\n| Language | Dockerfile |\n| Size | S |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nDefine multi-stage Dockerfile patterns for AgentCube's three core container images, optimizing for:\n\n1. **Build Separation**: Isolate Go compilation (builder stage) from runtime environment to reduce final image size\n2. **Security**: Run containers as non-root users with minimal runtime dependencies\n3. **Build Efficiency**: Leverage BuildKit cache mounts for Go module downloads to accelerate CI builds\n4. **Consistency**: Standardize Dockerfile structure across workloadmanager, router, and picod images\n\n**Target Images**:\n\n| Image | Binary | Runtime Base | User |\n|-------|--------|--------------|------|\n| `workloadmanager` | `./cmd/workload-manager` | `alpine:3.19` | `apiserver` (UID 1000) |\n| `agentcube-router` | `./cmd/router` | `alpine:3.19` | `router` (UID 1000) |\n| `picod` | `./cmd/picod` | `ubuntu:24.04` | `root` (sandbox permissions) |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Scope (范围)\n\n### 2.1 In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `docker/Dockerfile` | Multi-stage build for Workload Manager (builder → runtime) |\n| `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Multi-stage build for Router (builder → runtime) |\n| `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | Multi-stage build for PicoD (builder → runtime) |\n| `Makefile docker-* targets` | Build targets referencing Dockerfiles (already exist) |\n| Build args documentation | `TARGETOS`, `TARGETARCH` platform args for cross-compilation |\n\n### 2.2 Dockerfile Stage Structure\n\n**Workload Manager / Router (2-stage)**:\n\n| Stage | Base | Purpose |\n|-------|------|---------|\n| `builder` | `golang:1.24.9-alpine` | Go compilation with BuildKit cache mounts |\n| `runtime` | `alpine:3.19` | Minimal runtime with ca-certificates, non-root user |\n\n**PicoD (2-stage)**:\n\n| Stage | Base | Purpose |\n|-------|------|---------|\n| `builder` | `golang:1.24.4` | Go compilation |\n| `runtime` | `ubuntu:24.04` | Python3 dependency for sandbox execution, runs as root |\n\n### 2.3 Out of Scope\n\n| Item | Reason |\n|------|--------|\n| Multi-arch buildx configuration | Covered by existing `docker-buildx-*` Make targets |\n| Docker registry push logic | Covered by `docker-buildx-push-*` targets and CI workflow |\n| Helm chart image references | Chart values already reference correct image names |\n| Volcano scheduler image | Separate component with external image repository |\n| Distroless base images | Alpine/Ubuntu provide sufficient minimal runtime; distroless migration is separate AR |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n\n### 3.1 新增文件\n\n| File | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| N/A | Dockerfiles already exist in `docker/` directory |\n\n### 3.2 修改文件\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `docker/Dockerfile` | Validate existing multi-stage pattern; add BuildKit cache mount optimization |\n| `docker/Dockerfile.router` | Add `COPY client-go/ client-go/` for Go module dependencies; validate cache mounts |\n| `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | Validate builder → runtime stage separation; document root user requirement |\n| `Makefile` | Ensure `docker-build-*` targets pass correct build args (`TARGETOS`, `TARGETARCH`) |\n\n### 3.3 Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|------------|---------|\n| `golang:1.24.9-alpine` | Builder stage base image for Go compilation |\n| `golang:1.24.4` | Builder stage base for picod (matches Go version in CI) |\n| `alpine:3.19` | Minimal runtime base for workloadmanager/router |\n| `ubuntu:24.04` | Runtime base for picod (requires Python3 for sandbox) |\n| `ca-certificates` | TLS certificate bundle for HTTPS connections |\n\n### 3.4 Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| `CI: main.yml` | `make docker-build` builds workloadmanager image |\n| `CI: build-push-release.yml` | `make docker-buildx-push-*` pushes multi-arch images to ghcr.io |\n| `E2E: run_e2e.sh` | `make docker-build`, `docker-build-router`, `docker-build-picod` for Kind cluster |\n| `Helm chart` | References images by `repository:tag` from values.yaml |\n| `Kind cluster` | `kind load docker-image` loads local images for E2E testing |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n\n### Alternative 1: Single-stage Dockerfile (no builder separation)\n\n**Approach**: Build Go binary directly in runtime base image.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Simpler Dockerfile; fewer stages |\n| Cons | Final image includes Go toolchain (~300MB); larger attack surface; slower image pulls |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Multi-stage builds produce minimal runtime images (~20MB for Alpine-based) by excluding compiler and build dependencies.\n\n### Alternative 2: Distroless base images (gcr.io/distroless/static)\n\n**Approach**: Use distroless/static or distroless/base for runtime stage.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Smallest possible image; no shell/package manager; enhanced security |\n| Cons | Debugging harder (no shell); requires separate debug image for troubleshooting; picod needs Python3 (distroless/static insufficient) |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected for current scope. Alpine provides minimal footprint with shell for debugging. Distroless migration should be separate AR with debug image strategy.\n\n### Alternative 3: Shared builder stage via Dockerfile inheritance\n\n**Approach**: Create base builder Dockerfile and `FROM` it in component Dockerfiles.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Reduced duplication; centralized Go version management |\n| Cons | Dockerfile inheritance limited; BuildKit cache mounts require explicit declaration; additional base image build step |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Each Dockerfile should be self-contained for CI simplicity. Go version consistency managed via Makefile variables and CI workflow Go version pins.\n\n### Alternative 4: Static binary compilation with musl libc\n\n**Approach**: Compile with `-tags netgo,osusergo` for fully static binaries, use scratch base image.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Zero-dependency runtime; smallest image size; no libc version issues |\n| Cons | DNS resolution requires netgo tag; Go modules with CGO disabled; picod requires Python3 dependency |\n\n**Decision**: Partially adopted. `CGO_ENABLED=0` already used; Alpine (musl libc) provides static-like behavior without scratch complexity. Fully static binaries with scratch reserved for future optimization.\n\n### Alternative 5: Pre-built binary COPY (no in-container compilation)\n\n**Approach**: Build binaries outside Docker, COPY into runtime stage.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Faster builds if binaries cached; no Go image dependency |\n| Cons | Requires host Go toolchain matching target platform; CI complexity for cross-arch builds; reproducibility harder to guarantee |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. In-container compilation ensures consistent build environment, handles cross-platform compilation via `TARGETOS/TARGETARCH`, and leverages BuildKit layer caching.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Go version drift (builder vs CI) | CI workflow pins Go 1.24.4/1.24.9; Makefile docker targets align with Dockerfile base images |\n| Alpine libc DNS issues | Use `CGO_ENABLED=0` for static-like compilation; ca-certificates installed for TLS |\n| PicoD root user security | Documented requirement for sandbox permissions; sandbox pods isolate picod from host |\n| BuildKit cache invalidation | `go mod download` cache mount keyed by `go.mod/go.sum` hash; CI uses Buildx with cache export |\n| Image size bloat | Multi-stage ensures only binary copied to runtime; Alpine base ~5MB overhead |\n| Cross-arch build failures | Makefile `docker-buildx` targets use `--platform linux/amd64,arm64` with `TARGETOS/TARGETARCH` args |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Validate `docker/Dockerfile` multi-stage structure (builder → runtime)\n- [ ] Validate `docker/Dockerfile.router` includes `COPY client-go/ client-go/`\n- [ ] Validate `docker/Dockerfile.picod` uses `ubuntu:24.04` runtime with Python3\n- [ ] Verify BuildKit cache mounts: `--mount=type=cache,target=/go/pkg/mod`\n- [ ] Verify `CGO_ENABLED=0` in build command\n- [ ] Verify non-root user in workloadmanager/router runtime stages\n- [ ] Test `make docker-build` produces <50MB runtime image\n- [ ] Test `make docker-build-router` produces <50MB runtime image\n- [ ] Test `make docker-build-picod` produces functional image\n- [ ] Verify `TARGETOS=linux TARGETARCH=amd64` produces correct binary\n- [ ] Verify `TARGETOS=linux TARGETARCH=arm64` cross-compilation works\n- [ ] E2E test: `kind load docker-image` succeeds for all 3 images\n\n---\n\n## 7. References\n\n- Docker multi-stage builds: https://docs.docker.com/build/building/multi-stage/\n- BuildKit cache mounts: https://docs.docker.com/build/buildkit/#cache-mounts\n- Go cross-compilation: https://go.dev/doc/install/source#environment\n- deployment/design.md — Dockerfiles section (lines 157-178)\n- ci-cd/design.md — Build targets and CI workflow (lines 173-179)\n- deployment/spec.md — Docker images requirement (line 77-83)\n- manifests/charts/base/values.yaml — Image repository/tag defaults","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-032/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775886044036,"end":1775886044053}}}}
